reviews.text: So amazing! I had the most awesome birthday at Disney! On our trip we enjoyed the Magic Kingdom, Epcot, and Animal Kingdom, plus Typhoon Lagoon, Blizzard Beach, and Disney Springs. It was super fun and I can't wait to go back! Disney makes everything magical from "Happy Birthdays" to friendly "hellos" everyone on the cast is so friendly. Wonderful experience!

A wonderful, magical experience. From the arrival in the morning parking lot staff they deliver excellent so happy and  energetic they know how to make people feel so welcome. Inside park staff employees are so in sync with each other everyone are so happy! You can leave all your problems of the world behind you. I believe if Mr. Walt was alive everyone from parking lot staff to inside staff and every employee would of made him proud! That is his vision. Continue giving a magical experience to all. We love it every moment and memory we made. I recommend this place to everyone in the world for your family happy place. We will be returning again!!! Thank you Walt for your vision and dreams giving us a smile in our face and bring the youth out of us as well. Walt Disney World.

If you love Disney you are going to love it here. You hear about the magic of Disney and you get it as soon as you enter. Great for kids, adults, everyone!!! Staff are pleasant, polite, very nice,The parades are great, the grounds are clean and the landscaping is immaculate. Across all the Disney parks there is something for everyone to enjoy, and the firework displays at the end of the evening are brilliant. I've been to Florida Disney about ten times and each time is as good as the previous time.

Disney can be loads of fun, but requires planning and a strategy to get value for your money. I really don't like that you must now purchase tickets for the exact date (s) of your visit. Best way to do Disney is with annual pass combined with their phone app to set up fast passes. You pretty much need to pick your 3 fast passes that are allowed for the day 30 days in advance. Understand that people who reserve their room at a Disney property get many more advantages. If they buy tickets with their reservation, they can set up fast passes 60 days in advance. Those with disabilities will need to register with each park's guest services to be allowed "return time". All party members must go with that person to be included in the party. That means the disabled party goes to the gate keeper of an attraction's ride, they are issued a time to return and join the fast pass line. Only one return time may issed at a time. There is limit to size of party. Disabled person must badge through 1st in fast pass line.

We just got back from our week long vacation from Walt Disney in FL. We stayed at the All Stars Music resort. We had stayed at a Disney resorts ( Pop Century) last time and we were satisfied with the accommodation. The price for me was appropriate it included the  3 park tickets for 3 people. The room in their website   looks bigger than the actual room itself but true to the amenities as  listed. Comfortable bed and pillows makes a good night  sleep a welcome after a tiring day of walking at the park is well worth it. Expect that everything in Disney is a bit over priced especially if you drink bottled water. If your in for convenience having the meal plan might be the way to go for you and your family with several choices when you get to the parks itself but it might be pricey. If you’re in a budget then paying your meal as you go depends on your $ choice. The resort staff are friendly and approachable. Over all our stay was pleasant. And would  recommend it. They usually have great deals for a family of four!
